<TITLE> AL's Rafiqul Islam freed on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com)Former state minister for power, energy and mineral resources Rafiqul Islam was released on bail Thursday. The Awami League leader's son Mostafa Ashish Islam told bdnews24.com his father was released on bail from the prison ward at Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital at 2.30 pm. Deputy inspector general of prisons major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui was present at the time, said Mostafa. After leaving the hospital, the former state minister laid floral wreaths at the portrait of Bangabandhu in front of Bangabandhu Bhaban at Dhanmondi Road no 32. Rafiqul Islam was arrested on May 29 last year. He is accused in a corruption case against former prime minister Sheikh Hasina and others involving Candian oil-gas firm Niko Resources Ltd. bdnews
